Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery rosette bowl; interior glazed dark brown; exterior: brownish band at top of lip, part of dot-rosette below; inscribed on the outside, partly over rosette.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.837)
